<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700 Models - RADIATOR AND COMPONENT REMOVAL -
        Radiator Core
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Radiator Core</title>
        <para>After locating and securing the radiator assembly in a safely supported position on the floor or work
            bench area, remove the top frame mounting bolts (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1201040">Figure 40 and 41</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove upper frame bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate, loosen and remove the mounting bolts from the bottom of radiator cross frame.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the remainder of radiator frame bolts on each side of radiator.</para>
            <figure id="f1201040" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201040.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Radiator Frame Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR FRAME MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RADIATOR TOP FRAME</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After loosening and removing frame assembly bolts, support the radiator core and spread the
                radiator frame apart, away from core.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201041" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 41. Lower Radiator Frame Mounting Bolt Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR CORE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR SIDE FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RADIATOR STAY ROD MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. LOWER RADIATOR HOSE CONNECTION</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LOWER FRAME MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>6. RADIATOR BOTTOM FRAME</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lift and remove radiator core from radiator frame assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201042">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201042" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 42. Radiator Core Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR DRIVERS SIDE FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR PASSENGER SIDE FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>3. CHARGE AIR COOLER LOWER MOUNTING FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>4. RADIATOR LOWER HOSE CONNECTION</callout1>
                <callout1>5. RADIATOR CORE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove radiator lower frame assembly bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift and remove radiator core (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201042">Figure 42, Item 5</hotlnk>) from radiator frame assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove transmission oil cooler fittings (if applicable).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove core frame support brackets (sides).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove ground wire from radiator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Transfer all radiator fittings to new replacement core (if applicable).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
